{"title_page": "1985 LSU Tigers football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| mode = football\n| year = 1985\n| team = LSU Tigers\n| logo = \n| logo_size = \n| logo_alt = \n| conference = Southeastern Conference\n| short_conf = SEC\n| CoachRank = 20\n| APRank = 20\n| record = 9\u20132\u20131\n| conf_record = 4\u20131\u20131\n| head_coach = [[Bill Arnsparger]]\n| hc_year = 2nd\n| off_coach = [[Ed Zaunbrecher]]\n| oc_year = 2nd\n| stadium = [[Tiger Stadium (Baton Rouge)|Tiger Stadium]]\n| champion =\n| bowl = [[1985 Liberty Bowl|Liberty Bowl]]\n| bowl_result = L 7\u201321 vs. [[1985 Baylor Bears football team|Baylor]]\n}}\n{{1985 SEC football standings}}\nThe '''1985 LSU Tigers football team''' represented [[Louisiana State University]] during the [[1985 NCAA Division I-A football season]]. The team was led by [[Bill Arnsparger]] in his second season and finished with an overall record of nine wins, two losses, and one tie (9\u20132\u20131 overall, 4\u20131\u20131 in the SEC).\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 1985\n| poll = AP\n| timezone = Central\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 14\n| time = 12:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| away = y\n| rank = 12\n| opponent = [[1985 North Carolina Tar Heels football team|North Carolina]]\n| site_stadium = [[Kenan Memorial Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Chapel Hill, North Carolina|Chapel Hill, NC]]\n| tv = [[Pay-per-view|PPV]]\n| score = 23\u201313\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 21\n| time = 7:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = 9\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1985|team=Colorado State Rams|title=Colorado State}}\n| site_stadium = Tiger Stadium\n| site_cityst = [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana|Baton Rouge, LA]]\n| tv = PPV\n| score = 17\u20133\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 5\n| time = 7:00 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| rank = 8\n| opponent = [[1985 Florida Gators football team|Florida]]\n| op